						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-124064" number="36462" version="1611">
								<HEADING>§ 59-01 General.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16776" name="T15C059_59-01"/>§ 59-01 General.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124066" number="36463" version="2466">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(a)<TAB tab-count="1"/>Whenever a respondent is found in violation of any of the following provisions of the NYC Administrative Code, any civil penalties imposed by a hearing officer, pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-17" destination-id="0-0-0-11561">6-17</LINK>(a) in accordance with Section <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Inter Infobase Jump" destination-infobase-id="1813066185-672468487-0-0" destination-infobase-uil="L:\NY\New York City\Folio\Working\Charter.NFO" destination-infobase-name="" destination-infobase-title="" destination-name="1049-a" destination-id="0-0-0-0">1049-a</LINK>(d)(1)(d) of the Charter or any civil penalties imposed for admissions of violations, pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C006_6-09" destination-id="0-0-0-11539">6-09</LINK>(c) or late admissions, pursuant to 48 RCNY § <LINK style-name="Jump" style-name-escaped="Jump" style-id="0-0-0-31" type="Jump" destination-name="T48C003_3-17" destination-id="0-0-0-11433">3-17</LINK> will be imposed, pursuant to the penalty schedule set forth below. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-043]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124067" number="36464" version="1611">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(b)<TAB tab-count="1"/>All citations, unless otherwise indicated are to the NYC Administrative Code. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-043]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124068" number="36465" version="1611">
									<PARA>
										<TAB tab-count="1"/>(c)<TAB tab-count="1"/>A second violation is a violation by the same respondent of the same section of law with a date of occurrence within three (3) years of the date of occurrence of the previous violation. <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-043]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124065" number="36466" version="1611">
									<PARA>(Added City Record 10/30/2019, eff. 11/29/2019) <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-043]</HIGHLIGHTER>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
							</LEVEL>
						</LEVEL>
						<LEVEL style-name="Section" style-name-escaped="Section" style-id="0-0-0-486" level-depth="7" toc-section="true">
							<RECORD id="0-0-0-124069" number="36467" version="1611">
								<HEADING>§ 59-02 Hazardous Substances Emergency Response Law Penalty Schedule.</HEADING>
								<PARA>
									<DESTINATION id="0-0-0-16778" name="T15C059_59-02"/>§ 59-02 Hazardous Substances Emergency Response Law Penalty Schedule.</PARA>
							</RECORD>
							<LEVEL style-name="Normal Level" style-name-escaped="Normal-Level" style-id="0-0-0-0" level-depth="0" toc-section="false">
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124071" number="36468" version="1611">
									<PARA>* The following shall be considered environmentally sensitive areas: wetlands and wetland buffer areas; National and State parks; critical habitats for endangered and threatened plant and animal species; wilderness and natural areas; marine sanctuaries; conservation areas; preserves; wildlife areas; scenic, wild or recreational rivers; seashore and lakeshore recreational areas; critical biological resource areas; National and State protected and critical environmental areas (CEAS) as defined in 6 NYCRR Section 617.2(i). <HIGHLIGHTER style="highlighter-ALP" original-style-name="ALP" style-name-escaped="highlighter-ALP" name="ALP" id="0-0-0-33">[ALP S-043]</HIGHLIGHTER>
										<LINEBRK/>
									</PARA>
								</RECORD>
								<RECORD id="0-0-0-124070" number="36469" version="2497">
									<PARA>
										<TABLE>
											<TABLEFORMAT number-of-widths="4" left-border-space="0" left-border-width="30" left-border-color="#000000" right-border-space="0" right-border-width="30" right-border-color="#000000" top-border-space="0" top-border-width="30" top-border-color="#000000" bottom-border-space="0" bottom-border-width="30" bottom-border-color="#000000" horizontal-border-space="0" horizontal-border-width="15" horizontal-border-color="#000000" vertical-border-space="0" vertical-border-width="15" vertical-border-color="#000000">
												<COLUMNFORMAT column-width="20" percentage="yes"/>
